cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SE, cs.CY

Reasoning: 

1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - This is the most likely category as the paper proposes a security overlay protocol for existing 802.11 networks and discusses the vulnerability of the WEP protocol to security threats. 

2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This category is also likely as the paper focuses on the 802.11 standard and its ARQ protocol. 

3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - This category is relevant as the paper discusses the achievability of a vanishing secrecy outage probability in several realistic scenarios. 

4. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - This category is relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed protocol on the madwifi-ng driver. 

5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - This category is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the security implications of the WEP protocol and proposes a solution to improve network security.
